  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This synthetic adversarial package introduces W-CON-05: a VerificationActivity (mesh-independence study) is declared via hasVerificationActivity but no Evidence in the package carries prov:wasGeneratedBy pointing to that activity's IRI, leaving it as an orphan declaration.",
