    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps relative to MRL 5 requirements, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo UQ demonstrates 95th-percentile NIH predictions remain below clinical threshold with sufficient margin (0.61 vs. 0.80 g/100 L). Remaining factor gaps are acknowledged as epistemic limitations to be addressed in subsequent assessment cycles. The mesh independence study (declared via hasVerificationActivity) was cited as supporting discretization error control, though formal GCI documentation was not completed within this assessment cycle.",
